---
// Main content for marketplace/blockchain-database page
---

<div class="container-medium container-solution">
  <div class="solution-page-card">
    <div class="solution-page-content-wrapper">
      <div class="integration-content-copy">
        <div class="top-content integration-card-top-content">
          <div class="split-solution-header">
            <div class="image-wrapper integration-icon-wrapper">
              <div class="solution-template-icon"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="split-content integration-details">
              <div class="integration-title-wrapper">
                <h1 class="title h2-size integration-name">Blockchain Database</h1>
              </div>
              <p class="paragraph integration-about-excerpt">
                A single API to use the blockchain as your data layer — write immutable records with a Certificate of
                Trust, or use it as a queryable, updateable hash table. No wallets, no gas fees, no infrastructure to
                run.
              </p>
              <div class="split-button-solution">
                <div class="collection-list-wrapper w-dyn-list" style="margin-left: auto;">
                  <div role="list" class="collection-list w-dyn-items w-row">
                    <div role="listitem" class="collection-item w-dyn-item w-col w-col-3">
                      <div style="background-color: #af89ee" class="div-block-9">
                        <div class="link-text">Polygon</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div role="listitem" class="collection-item w-dyn-item w-col w-col-3">
                      <div style="background-color: hsla(20, 100%, 54.02%, 1)" class="div-block-9">
                        <div class="link-text">Matchain</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="split-content integration-card-content">
          <div
            data-duration-in="300"
            data-duration-out="100"
            data-current="Description"
            data-easing="ease"
            class="integration-tabs w-tabs"
          >
            <div class="integration-tabs-menu w-tab-menu">
              <a data-w-tab="Description" class="integration-tab-link w-inline-block w-tab-link w--current"
                ><div>Description</div></a
              ><a
                data-w-tab="Tab Support"
                class="integration-tab-link last w-inline-block w-condition-invisible w-tab-link"
                ><div>Contact Support</div></a
              >
            </div>
            <div class="integrations-tabs-content w-tab-content">
              <div data-w-tab="Description" class="integration-tab w-tab-pane w--tab-active">
                <div class="rich-text w-richtext">
                  <p>
                    <strong>Blockchain Database</strong> turns the blockchain into a drop-in data layer for your
                    application. A single REST API lets you anchor full records immutably with a Certificate of Trust,
                    or use the chain as a trusted hash table — read, write, and update keyed values with the same
                    durability guarantees a public ledger gives you. Wallets, gas, and chain selection are handled
                    behind the scenes.
                  </p>
                  <h3><strong>Features</strong></h3>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>
                      <strong>Single Write API</strong><br />Send a single REST request specifying the network and
                      payload. The same endpoint anchors immutable records or upserts hash-table entries — pick the
                      mode per call.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Hash-Table Mode</strong><br />Use the blockchain as a queryable, updateable key/value
                      store. Anchor your customers&#x27; most important records on-chain and update them as state
                      evolves, without losing the audit trail of every prior version.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Certificate of Trust</strong><br />Every immutable write produces a verifiable
                      certificate that proves what was stored, when, and by whom — ready to share with auditors,
                      regulators, or end customers.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Data Retrieval</strong><br />Fetch any stored record on demand — by transaction, by key,
                      or by version — so your data is always accessible when you need it.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Seamless Wallet Management</strong><br />BWS handles wallet provisioning and signing for
                      every chain operation behind the scenes — your application never touches a private key.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Automated Fee Management</strong><br />No gas accounting, no native-token reserves to
                      maintain. Our API calculates and pays network fees automatically and bills them transparently.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Multi-Chain by Default</strong><br />Deploy the same call to Polygon or Matchain by
                      changing a single parameter — pick the network that fits your cost, latency, and trust profile.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3><strong>Benefits</strong></h3>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>
                      <strong>Two Modes, One API</strong><br />Immutable anchoring and hash-table storage are exposed
                      through the same surface — start with one, add the other when your use case grows, no
                      re-integration required.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Quick and Easy Integration</strong><br />Designed so any developer can ship a
                      blockchain-backed feature without prior Web3 experience.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Boost Trust and Transparency</strong><br />Anchoring data on a public chain gives
                      customers, partners, and regulators independently verifiable proof of what your system did and
                      when.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Use the blockchain as the data layer behind your most trust-sensitive workflows — from
                    record-keeping and certification to live customer-facing state.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div data-w-tab="Tab Support" class="integration-tab w-tab-pane">
                <div class="w-layout-hflex">
                  <div class="div-block-22">
                    <div class="code-embed-2 w-embed w-script">
                      <script
                        type="module"
                        src="https://interfaces.zapier.com/assets/web-components/zapier-interfaces/zapier-interfaces.esm.js"
                      ></script>
                      <zapier-interfaces-page-embed
                        page-id=""
                        no-background="true"
                        style="max-width: 900px; height: 900px"></zapier-interfaces-page-embed>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="div-block-21">
                    <h2>Need support?</h2>
                    <p>Fill the form and we will contact you.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="inline integration-card">
            <div class="coming-soon w-condition-invisible"><div class="text-block-13">Coming Soon</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
